            "gitPatch": {
              "unidiffPatch": "diff --git a/.jules/sentinel.md b/.jules/sentinel.md\nindex 0097a32..2595c1d 100644\n--- a/.jules/sentinel.md\n+++ b/.jules/sentinel.md\n@@ -15,3 +15,7 @@\n **Vulnerability:** The HTTP API server in `crates/mapmap-control/src/web/server.rs` used the legacy header `X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block`. This feature is deprecated across modern browsers and is considered an anti-pattern as it can introduce new vulnerabilities like selective blocklist-based side-channel leaks.\n **Learning:** Using `X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block` can sometimes allow attackers to disable legitimate scripts on the page by tricking the browser's XSS auditor into blocking them (an XSS-Auditor bypass/denial-of-service). Modern applications should rely exclusively on Content Security Policy (CSP).\n **Prevention:** Always set `X-XSS-Protection: 0` to disable the legacy auditor and enforce strong CSP headers instead for XSS defense-in-depth.\n+## 2024-05-24 - DoS by NaN Panic in Sorting\n+**Schwachstelle:** Die Verwendung von `unwrap()` beim Sortieren von Fließkommazahlen (z.B. in `mapping.rs` für Tiefe oder `animation.rs` für Marker-Zeit) mittels `partial_cmp()` führte zu potenziellen Panics. Wenn die berechneten Fließkommazahlen `NaN` (Not a Number) waren (etwa durch fehlerhafte externe Daten, User-Inputs oder Animationen), ergab `partial_cmp()` `None`, was von `unwrap()` zu einem Panic eskaliert wurde.\n+**Lektion:** Fließkommazahlen, die in Sortier-Schleifen genutzt werden und durch externe Parameter beeinflusst werden, können NaN werden. `unwrap()` auf `partial_cmp` ist in Rust ein bekanntes DoS-Risiko.\n+**Prävention:** Bei `partial_cmp` von floats, insbesondere aus dem Vorce-Datenmodell, immer `unwrap_or(std::cmp::Ordering::Equal)` oder explizites Pattern Matching verwenden, damit Sortierungen auch bei korrupten (NaN) Werten robust weiterlaufen.\ndiff --git a/crates/vorce-core/src/animation.rs b/crates/vorce-core/src/animation.rs\nindex d03e6b4..b2c62fb 100644\n--- a/crates/vorce-core/src/animation.rs\n+++ b/crates/vorce-core/src/animation.rs\n@@ -378,8 +378,12 @@ impl AnimationClip {\n     /// Add a timeline marker to the clip\n     pub fn add_marker(&mut self, marker: TimelineMarker) {\n         self.markers.push(marker);\n-        self.markers\n-            .sort_by(|a, b| a.time.partial_cmp(&b.time).unwrap());\n+        // SAFETY: Fallback to Equal to prevent panics on NaN values (DoS protection)\n+        self.markers.sort_by(|a, b| {\n+            a.time\n+                .partial_cmp(&b.time)\n+                .unwrap_or(std::cmp::Ordering::Equal)\n+        });\n     }\n \n     /// Remove a timeline marker by time in seconds\ndiff --git a/crates/vorce-core/src/mapping.rs b/crates/vorce-core/src/mapping.rs\nindex 0ffeeee..4bcbb5e 100644\n--- a/crates/vorce-core/src/mapping.rs\n+++ b/crates/vorce-core/src/mapping.rs\n@@ -134,7 +134,12 @@ impl MappingManager {\n             self.mappings.iter().filter(|m| m.is_renderable()).collect();\n \n         // Sort by depth (back to front)\n-        mappings.sort_by(|a, b| a.depth.partial_cmp(&b.depth).unwrap());\n+        // SAFETY: Fallback to Equal to prevent panics on NaN values (DoS protection)\n+        mappings.sort_by(|a, b| {\n+            a.depth\n+                .partial_cmp(&b.depth)\n+                .unwrap_or(std::cmp::Ordering::Equal)\n+        });\n \n         mappings\n     }\n",
              "baseCommitId": "4b1c517a56a982fb81560d5c758c327068ee0bd0",
