      "outputs": [
        {
          "changeSet": {
            "source": "sources/github/MrLongNight/MapFlow",
            "gitPatch": {
              "unidiffPatch": "diff --git a/.jules/bolt.md b/.jules/bolt.md\nindex edb5ec5..0950918 100644\n--- a/.jules/bolt.md\n+++ b/.jules/bolt.md\n@@ -1,7 +1,7 @@\n-## 2024-05-24 - [Avoid Intermediate HashSets for Small Lookups]\n-**Learning:** In Rust loops, mapping an array of values into a `HashSet` to perform an `O(1)` `.contains()` check is an anti-pattern when the data set is small and the loop runs frequently (like in media orchestration ticks). The allocation overhead and hashing cost far outweigh a simple `O(N)` linear `.find()`.\n-**Action:** Avoid temporary `HashSet` allocations for small cross-referencing tasks in hot loops; rely on direct iterator methods instead. Also ensure ownership transfer is favored over `.clone()` when the source variable is no longer needed.\n+## 2026-04-08 - String allocations in tight loops\n+**Learning:** In immediate-mode UI rendering loops like `build_node_catalog`, calling `String::to_lowercase()` inside a `.filter()` closure causes O(N) heap allocations per frame, drastically degrading performance.\n+**Action:** Pre-compute lowercased string variants directly in the base struct and cache dynamically built collections using `std::sync::OnceLock` so the initialization and string allocations run exactly once per application lifecycle.\n \n-## 2025-03-25 - [Redundant String Allocation in Loops]\n-**Learning:** Found a common pattern in UI filtering where `String::to_lowercase()` was called inside a `.filter()` iterator closure. This causes O(N) heap allocations during search operations, degrading UI performance with large media libraries.\n-**Action:** Always pre-compute and cache string transformations like `to_lowercase()` in the corresponding models (e.g. `MediaItem`, `EffectPreset`, `MediaEntry`) instead of dynamically calling `to_lowercase()` inside `filter()` closures during UI searches. This significantly reduces allocations and speeds up query operations.\n+## 2026-04-08 - Scratchpad file contamination\n+**Learning:** The testing of standard libraries like `OnceLock` via scratchpad files (e.g. `test_once_lock.rs`) can result in artifacts (source and compiled binary) polluting the working directory and being inadvertently staged during the pull request creation process if a global `git commit -am` or `git add .` is executed.\n+**Action:** Always delete scratchpad files (`rm test_once_lock test_once_lock.rs`) explicitly immediately after their execution, or run them in an isolated temporary directory outside the main repository workspace.\ndiff --git a/crates/vorce-control/src/osc/address.rs b/crates/vorce-control/src/osc/address.rs\nindex c85c17b..520155c 100644\n--- a/crates/vorce-control/src/osc/address.rs\n+++ b/crates/vorce-control/src/osc/address.rs\n@@ -237,8 +237,11 @@ mod tests {\n         assert_eq!(target1, ControlTarget::LayerOpacity(0));\n \n         // Test /mapmap/\n-        let target2 = parse_osc_address(\"/mapmap/layer/5/position\").unwrap();\n-        assert_eq!(target2, ControlTarget::LayerPosition(5));\n+        let target2 = parse_osc_address(\"/mapmap/layer/5/position\");\n+        assert!(\n+            target2.is_err(),\n+            \"Legacy namespace /mapmap/ should return an error\"\n+        );\n     }\n \n     use super::*;\ndiff --git a/crates/vorce-ui/src/core/config.rs b/crates/vorce-ui/src/core/config.rs\nindex c74e23b..1fb3f62 100644\n--- a/crates/vorce-ui/src/core/config.rs\n+++ b/crates/vorce-ui/src/core/config.rs\n@@ -521,9 +521,7 @@ impl UserConfig {\n         })\n     }\n \n-    fn resolve_existing_config_path(\n-        primary: Option\u003cPathBuf\u003e,\n-    ) -\u003e Option\u003cPathBuf\u003e {\n+    fn resolve_existing_config_path(primary: Option\u003cPathBuf\u003e) -\u003e Option\u003cPathBuf\u003e {\n         primary.as_ref().filter(|path| path.exists()).cloned()\n     }\n \n@@ -785,6 +783,3 @@ mod tests {\n         assert!(!config.set_active_layout(\"does-not-exist\"));\n     }\n }\n-st\"));\n-    }\n-}\ndiff --git a/crates/vor