              "suggestedCommitMessage": "⚡ Bolt: Fix Unicode Case-Folding & Avoid Zero-Alloc Hacks\n\nThis commit addresses a performance vs. correctness issue in the search implementations within rendering loops (`shortcuts_panel.rs`, `quick_create.rs`, and `search.rs`). \n\nThe previous implementation relied on an ASCII-only zero-allocation byte window hack (`eq_ignore_ascii_case`) which breaks Unicode case-folding (such as Umlaute). To fix the Unicode support without re-introducing O(N) heap allocations for every frame when no search is active, the implementation now uses lazy evaluation:\n\n`if filter.is_empty() { return true; }`\n\nBy checking if the search query is empty before allocating a lowercase string (`to_lowercase()`), the overhead is completely avoided in the default state, while ensuring proper case-insensitive search for international characters when a user actually enters a query. \n\nThis change preserves performance in the normal hot loop state while guaranteeing functionally correct results. The `.jules/bolt.md` journal has been updated with these specific codebase insights."
